===Etymology===
{{ja-kanjitab|すみ|yomi=k}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=すみ|-}}, first appearing in the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' of 720 {{CE}} with the phonetic spelling {{m|ojp||須彌}} {{IPAfont|⟨sumi<sub>1</sub>⟩}}.<ref name="KDJ2-ink">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|墨}}</ref> Cognate with {{m|ja|すみ#Japanese:_charcoal|炭|tr=sumi|[[charcoal]]}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref>

In turn, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|sort=すみ|*sumi}}.  Cognate with {{cog|ams|墨|tr=sïmi}}.

Possibly derived from the [[homophonous]] {{m|ja|連用形|tr=ren'yōkei||continuative or stem form}} {{m|ja|済み|tr=sumi}} of verb {{m|ja|済む|tr=sumu||to finish, to conclude}}, from the way that [[cinder]]s are left after a fire has finished burning.

Possibly also related to {{m|ja|煤|tr=susu||[[soot]]}}, from which [[India ink]] is made.

